advanced features in our system fonts, and learn best practices for using custom fonts.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","type":"topic"},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2016/805":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2016\/805","checksum":null,"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2016\/805","type":"download"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","title":"WWDC Notes","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Learn More…","type":"text"}],"title":"Learn More…","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"alt":null,"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png"}],"type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-802-Designing-for-tvOS":{"title":"Designing for tvOS","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-802-designing-for-tvos","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-802-Designing-for-tvOS","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Change the way the world experiences television through apps that are designed to be immersive, intuitive and easy to use. Learn best practices and techniques to take advantage of the big screen and the Siri Remote."}],"type":"topic","role":"sampleCode","kind":"article"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-804-Designing-Great-Apple-Watch-Experiences":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-804-designing-great-apple-watch-experiences","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-804-Designing-Great-Apple-Watch-Experiences","title":"Designing Great Apple Watch Experiences","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"text":"watchOS 3 represents a big leap forward for Apple Watch and the apps that run on it. Performance improvements, powerful graphics and animation capabilities, deeper access to device capabilities, and a refined navigation model lay the foundation for designing useful and stunning Apple Watch apps. Learn best practices and techniques for making complications, notifications and apps that are highly actionable, glanceable and responsive.","type":"text"}]}}}